## Perils of lack of sleep

* a week of sleep deprivation (less than 6 hours per night) leads to hundreds of genes switching off. These genes are responsible, among other things for immune system, and resistance to stress. A week of proper sleep reverses these changes, but there is a hypothesis that prolonged periods of sleep derpivation can lead to obesity and heart disease. After [a story in The Telegraph](http://www.telegraph.co.uk/science/science-news/9892792/Lack-of-sleep-switches-off-genes.html).